.TH GIT-STAGE-BATCH-SKIP 1 "May 2026" "git-stage-batch @VERSION@" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
git-stage-batch-skip \- defer selected live changes
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B git-stage-batch skip
[\fB\-\-line\fR \fIIDS\fR]
[\fB\-\-file\fR [\fIPATH\fR] | \fB\-\-files\fR \fIPATTERN\fR...]
[\fB\-\-auto\-advance\fR|\fB\-\-no\-auto\-advance\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B skip
marks live changes as skipped without staging or removing them. Skipped hunks
can be revisited with
.BR "git-stage-batch again" .
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BI "\-\-line, \-\-lines " IDS
Skip only specific displayed line IDs.
.TP
.B \-\-file
.RI [ PATH ]
Skip all hunks from one file. If
.I PATH
is omitted, use the selected hunk's file.
.TP
.BI "\-\-files " PATTERN "..."
Skip all changed files matched by gitignore-style patterns.
.TP
.B \-\-auto\-advance
Select the next hunk after the command completes.
.TP
.B \-\-no\-auto\-advance
Leave no hunk selected after the command completes.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR git-stage-batch (1),
.BR git-stage-batch-again (1),
.BR git-stage-batch-include (1)
